{
  "texts": [
    "Facial expression recognition (FER) is a computer vision technique used to recognize a human's psychological state and emotions from an image or video sequence [130].",
    "This makes it a practical tool for robots to automatically comprehend and recognize human facial expressions for better interactions.",
    "With the popularity of machine learning, recent studies have employed deep neural networks to decipher the emotions conveyed by facial expressions in an image [131].",
    "These networks require large training datasets from real-world scenarios to handle emotion recognition in the wild.",
    "Overall, FER holds great potential for advancing the field of human-computer interaction, especially in the development of emotionally intelligent robots."
  ]
}